          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Student Loan Opportunity Act of 2015</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code, with respect to tax-exempt private activity bond financing, to: (1) eliminate the restriction on nonprofit corporations that acquire student loan notes to notes incurred under the Higher Education Act of 1965 (thus allowing such corporations to access tax-exempt financing for other types of student loans), and (2) expand the operations of such corporations to include performing student assistance related activities.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2015-10-23T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
